nodes.title: Output Path
widgets_values:
• Batch Range: Set the Batch Range - How much your PC can render at a time. Default is 24. 
Use Lower around 5 when doing a 720p to 4k conversion, To prevent going out of memory 

• Video Settings: Set Fame Load Cap size to 24 if you want to test out different models. 


Do not downscale using force size, it introduces dicey pixels after upscale.

nodes.title: Batch Size
widgets_values: • Set the Duration of the Video in frames

This workflow produces Legacy Animatediff Animations using SD 1.5 Models 

How to Use: 

1) Input Output Folder, Set Dimensions, Set Batch Size, Load Checkpoint and Lora
2) Select AnimateDiff Model
3) Enter Positive, and Negative Prompts.
4) [Optional] Enable and Set OpenPose Settings.
5) Set Ksampler Settings
6) Set Export Video Settings [FPS, FileName]

Min PC requirements - 16 GB Ram and 6GB GPU. [Use Lower Batch Range or Use 2_2) Video2Image Upscaler Using AnimateDiff]
